I shaved my beard off for 2023!! I went from the second  photo - a grizzly man - to the first one, cleaned up. Needed to mix things up, get freshened up!!! Let's go!!! #haircut #beardcut #refresh #acting #actor #writing #writer #2023

Had a beautiful time shooting @ncishawaiicbs and thank you @vanessalachey for the amazing and kind gifts welcoming me to your show. Got to work with @levar.burton again but the photos I took with him I can't show yet! Once it airs! Amazing cast and crew, and a wonderful actress you're all going to love!!! ##### Now, flying to Ireland from Hawaii, through SFO and London to shoot a feature. Will post soon!

Just did an interview with @castingnetworks talking all things @ncis_cbs @ncisla @ncisnola and my upcoming episode on @ncishawaiicbs - plus slid in a t-shirt I got from the amazing @lanai and the dope brand out of Hawaii @88teesofficial - and yes Lanai, I mentioned you by name, (and Brooke Lee too! Does she have an insta page? Couldn't find it if so). Will share the link to the interview when it comes out probably next month! Let's go!! And thank you @vanessalachey for the amazing hat!!!!! So much love!!!!! Aloha aloha aloha!!!

Riding through Thailand was amazing, and doing the on camera hosting the BMW GS Trophy was incredible. Keeping up with the super fast riders, experiencing the fun but the best is getting to know the locals, the culture and beautiful country.  So many good memories! #motorcycle #bmw @bmwmotorrad @touratechusa  @alpinestarsadventure @marmot and more!!

Thanks to @castingnetworks for a wonderful piece, and as always @kyrani for the amazing shots. # Shout out to @kennedycasting for starting all of this mess 😂❤️ with casting me in my first NCIS role, to @claudlyon who's a staunch advocate for Disabilty inclusion, to @cbsentdiversity @cbstvstudios @cbstv @tsmithanoai for pushing those boundaries, and all the wonderful directors, producers, writers I've worked with over the years in this universe. @noahevslin @ktbeattie @skandanderson @levar.burton @danielaruah @ericcolsen @darylchillmitchell @csilber928 and so many others. And for organizations pushing this topic - @inevitablefoundation @1in4coalition @respecttheability @disabilityfilmchallenge (going on now!!!!) @rudermanfamilyfoundation @jayruderman and so many others. Long way to go, lots of work to do, but some powerful folks seeing Disabilty as a valuable and normal life experience for amazing stories in film and television yet to be told. Let's go!!!

Thank you for the wonderfully written article @variety and for the coverage, to @claudlyon for amazing quotes, @cbstv @cbsentdiversity @tsmithanoai and the whole team, and all the people supporting along this journey. Much love!!! Check out the full article on Variety.com

Luminate came out with a National Disability Awareness Month  Data Celebration of Creative Innovators and I made the list with some really amazing people like my homie @nicnovicki . I don't post about being a writer as much as I should, but I will here, if you're interested, read on. Wrote several features, on the @theblcklst , another optioned by dircetor Henry Jacobson of Bloodline, another with a financing company currently attaching a dircetor (y'all directors should reach out if you like sci-fi), wrote a pilot for a show with a major studio, have my other slated projects with my lit manager and they're buzzing around, wrote with @alexjbarone 130 - 3 minute skit style episodes of @tommyandbobbyshow - produced those which are out on the link above, more edits soon, have multiple writing samples and dipping all my five toes into writing a romcom because behind the rough exterior I'm a big baby. So yeah, I write. ######## #acting #writing #producing #amputee #disabled #disability #ifyoudontknownowyouknow

Woah! I had a wonderful time at @campnolimits playing disc golf and spending time with young people and families with limb loss. The camp is all about sport, healthy living and discovering new ways to have a blast! With @innovadiscs we're launching a collaboration "Kurt Yaeger" disk which all proceeds are donated to the camp. So, when we're ready, I'll share the information and you can get an office Innova/Kurt Yaeger collaboration disk and at the same time support @campnolimits !!! More to come. #innova #diskgolf #golf #disk #campnolimits #amputee #limb #limbloss #nostopping #camp @chrisbrophy33 is the man!!! And @alexjbarone for his long service and dedication to the camp and the kids/families! Let's go!!!!

Harrison Ford stole my pose for his @Esquire shoot. 😎😎 Well, he called me to ask if it was cool, and I was like, "yeah, it's cool". 🙄 celebrities... #harrisonford #kurtyaeger #actor #esquire Kurt Yaeger original shot by the amazing photographer @kyrani Who did it better, Harrison or me?
Hiking out near Lone Pine, collecting minerals like Amazonite, other Plagioclase pieces, and enjoying the new @willowwoodglobal foot. Y'all should check out that and their liner. Epic!!

Rocking shorts on the carpet for @darumamovie - my good buddies @jwlawson57 and @tobiaseasyforrest are the leads in this (I believe) first ever double leading role of two actors with a Disabilty, with the best part being the story has nothing to do with the Disabilty!!!! The writer/director combo Alex and Kelli said it best: "this film is about what people can do, what they can accomplish, and how they grow as people", I love it. I'll post more photos when I get them of the directors/actors too. Look forward to seeing it play other spots @newportbeachfilmfest and @tiff_net and more!!

Met with with my homie @johnconnorsactor and @carl_quinn_cinematographer for their powerful and much needed film @the_black_guelph_film - about inter-generational traumatic fallout from abuse. Psychologically makes you step inside the shoes of someone dealing with the incongruent thought process of the post traumatic mind. Powerful. #movie #film #films #actor #acting @danceswithfilms
Still love this day riding in the mountains with awesome folks hooked up by @alpinestarsadventure and @alpinestars Love ripping in the dirt, one leg or not!!! #motorcycle #amputee #doit
She said yes. @stefanieterzo

Look at the smile on my face, and on all the kids. This is what I want to bring to everyone at @campnolimits and you can too by supporting and purchasing a "Kurt Yaeger" collaboration disc from the amazing @innovadiscs . I'll put a link in my bio for this and/or you can go to @innovaproshop to find it there too. Very excited to join up and raise money for a wonderful charity that brings so many smiles!!! Thanks @alexjbarone for showing me the great work everyone, including you, do here!!! #discgolf #amputee #disabled #charity #support #fundraise #letsgo!

We believe enjoying disc golf is possible for any type of body, almost regardless of disability. Innova has teamed up with actor and X Games athlete @kurtyaeger to help raise funds for a cause close to his heart, @campnolimits . The No Limits Foundation is a non-profit organization 501 (c)(3) providing camps for children with limb loss and differences. The camp aims to provide education, mentorship, and support to these children and their families. Disc golf has become an important part of Camp No Limits’ activities, as it provides a unique challenge that is adaptable to the needs of each specific individual. 
Help Kurt and Innova spread some disc golf love by picking up these exclusive Halo fundraiser discs - link in bio. 💛 #discgolf #campnolimits #innovadiscs

You can still help out @campnolimits get a cool "Kurt Yaeger"
Disk from @innovadiscs / @innovaproshop and have some satisfaction of throwing me around, it the ground, wall, or whatever destructive impulse my face or name inspires you to do. 😂😂😂😂 I just figured, since I've died in so many TV shows, there must be something about this face!!!! #discgolf #discgolfcoaches #discgolflife #discgolfeveryday @udiscapp @discgolf @bubbawatson @typeters39 @chefaz @wesdrummer @bertkreischer @aj_rivera_artist @kevinmalejandro @khivju let's go!!! Spread, share, buy and play!!! My baby smiling in the background :) @stefanieterzo -

Like, give a thumbs up in the comments if you want change - -“There has been no change in the representation of characters with disabilities since this community was included in our reporting across top films from 2015,” the report concludes. “Characters with disabilities are consistently missing in film.” --- no change. ---- let that sink in ---- no change ----- So when someone tells you there is a problem with Disabilty representation, and they tell you how to fix it, try not to blow them off or spout off about 1 good example you can come up with where representation happened. It isn't good enough. You can't continue doing the status quo and think anything will change. Force the change and if people aren't along for the forcing, leave them behind.

I found the gal who likes my flaws, helps me grow and learn, is immensely patient, warm, loving and supports me when I'm shaken - @stefanieterzo thanks for saying yes. With loving family and friends around, the romantic venue @outpostbigbear it was a magical day of fun and joy. Thanks to Carl, Mel, Amanda, my brothers, brother-in-law, Fern and family, and so so many others for a wonderful experience. Much love!!! - more photos to come

Episode 7 with Kurt Yaeger is out now on all streaming platforms! Please check it out on Apple Podcast, Google Podcast, Spotify, Amazon Music or wherever you stream podcasts! Get the transcript in Spanish and English on the website linked in bio. 

Kurt Yaeger is an American actor and disability advocate known for his inspiring story of resilience and determination. He was born on January 3, 1977, in San Francisco, California. However, in 2006, his life took a dramatic turn when he was involved in a motorcycle accident that resulted in the amputation of his left leg.
Despite this life-altering event, Kurt Yaeger continued to pursue his passion for acting and quickly established himself as a talented actor in the entertainment industry. He's best known for his roles in popular TV shows like "Sons of Anarchy" and "Quarry." His acting career has also included roles in films and other television series.
Kurt Yaeger is not only known for his acting career but also for his dedication to advocating for disability rights and representation in the entertainment industry. He has been an outspoken advocate for disabled individuals, working to promote inclusivity and diversity in both Hollywood and society at large.
His personal journey from a motorcycle accident to a successful acting career and advocacy work serves as an inspiration to many, and he continues to use his platform to make a positive impact on the lives of people with disabilities and to challenge stereotypes and prejudices. Kurt Yaeger is a testament to the power of determination and perseverance in the face of adversity.

Tune into this conversation to hear more about disability in acting, exclusive content about NCIS, and disability advocacy in Hollywood.
